Welcome to Hale Kailani (Heavenly Waters House) Indoor and outdoor living come together seamlessly in this furnished home. Beautiful mature landscaping welcomes you and surrounds the house. Enjoy staying in a spacious waterfront home on Paiko Lagoon with views out to the Pacific Ocean. This very special area on the Kanewai and Paiko Lagoons is where Princess Kaiulani held one of her large birthday parties and the area where King Kamehameha I and his favorite wife lived using Kanewai Lagoon as their private fish pond.  Now guests from around the world can continue to enjoy this area, the lovely Old Hawaii-style home and the private swimming pool.  Enjoy the lagoon view from the expansive covered patio or from the hammock hanging between two coconut trees in the large grassy private yard. This home is perfect for people who want extra space, a very private location and a secure, gated entry. The indoor dining table seats 10 and there's room for informal eating at both the kitchen peninsula or the outdoor dining tables. A fully-stocked kitchen is great for preparing meals in house or enjoy nearby restaurants that are less than a mile away, including: Roy's, Outback Steakhouse, Pailaka Grill, Bowles Burritos, Gyotako Japanese Restaurant, Le Bistro or CafÃ© Asia. Kahala Mall, Costco and Hawaii Kai shopping centers are just 10 minutes drive from this home. The house also features air conditioning and two office desks for people who wish to stay connected. There's indoor laundry for guests to use and three full bathrooms. Two bedrooms feature King-size beds and a bedroom in between features a double bed. Two full bathrooms with large showers are between the three bedrooms with a third bathroom being off the kitchen. Rent includes electricity, water/sewer, cable tv, internet, pool & yard service. Pets are negotiable.   6-Month or 1-Year Renewable Lease, Tenant pays Rent + GE tax of 4.712%.   With leases less than 180 days, Tenant pays Rent + GE tax of 4.712% + TA tax of 10.25%. This fully furnished and restored two-story Hibiscus Manor is part of a stunning private retreat in the heart of Honolulu - Na Pua Lani - the Heavenly Flowers - is truly a one-of-a-kind Hawaiian Estate comprised of three separate elegant houses. The "Hibiscus Manor" is an incredible restoration of an early 1918 classic residence and is the largest home with over 3000sq.ft., 5 bedrooms and 3 full bathrooms plus a half bath. The home can sleep up to 10 guests comfortably. Enjoy the sophisticated tropical design and furnishings along with the exquisite craftsmanship of old Hawaii and views toward Diamond Head. A basement bedroom has it's own entry door as well as interior stairs to the main house - the perfect getaway for someone wanting a bit more privacy. The large 36' x 17' saltwater pool is surrounded with tropical landscaping and complete with songbirds that live there too. The large lanai is the perfect place to relax overlooking the pool with a charming office at one end is the ideal place to get a bit of work done. This home is fully furnished and stocked in the Old Hawaiian Style, including Hawaiian quilts, linens and kitchenware so you will not need to bring anything. There's garage parking, pool/beach toys & a gas BBQ included by the pool as well. All utilities are included in the rent, even high-speed internet and HD Cable TV. The Kaimuki Neighborhood is close to sandy beaches. The famous Waikiki Beach is only an 8 minute drive away. Diamond Head and Manoa are also close by. The Na Pua Lani Estate is in a peaceful, charming neighborhood known for its niche shops, specialty boutiques and award-winning eateries along the main thoroughfare of Waialae Avenue. This homes' unique character and prime location make it a wonderful place to live, work, play and visit. Whether you grew up on island, or you have just arrived, Kapolei welcomes all to the sunniest, friendliest corner of Oahu with all the amenities and comforts of the Mainland but with the mindset of Hawai'i.   Kapolei Lofts, a resort-style community situated in the heart of Kapolei. In the evenings, you jaunt over to Kapolei Commons for a gourmet dinner and movie. On the weekends you toy with which of the dozens of picture-perfect beaches to lounge at, or maybe you hit the links at Kapolei Golf Club. The kids can play the day away at Kapiolani Regional Park (just a few blocks) or celebrate the constant summer weather at Wet & Wild water park.  When family and friends visit, Disney's Aulani and the Four Seasons resorts are minutes away from them. And for those days you just want a quiet coffee and a good book, you are mere steps from a Coffee Bean & Tea Leaf.  But most importantly, after a long day of work, you can rest assured that you will instantly relax at your resort-style community. Show off your stylish clubhouse with a friendly potluck or wine night, float the day away in our massive pool, or get heart-healthy in our state-of-the-art fitness center. This is your home. You deserve to be spoiled. When you are in this apartment, you feel the essence of Hawaii. Diamond Head is sitting in your lap and all that is between you and her is an expansive green area containing the zoo and parks. Enjoy your morning coffee on the huge lanai/balcony listening to the occasional faint call of the baboons from the zoo. Enchanting!   THE APARTMENT  The apartment is air conditioned, but you rarely need it given the balmy trade winds sweeping off the ocean.   If the breeze and a view are not enough luxury, the apartment is covered from toe to toe in travertine and slate stone. This is low maintenance, clean, and beautiful on the eyes. The apartment doors are made from high quality koa wood, with air vents across the top to let in plenty of Hawaii's clean fresh breezes.  The apartment has all newer appliances, including a microwave, dishwasher, ceramic top oven, and washer/dryer. The bathroom is sparkling clean with a newer sink and toilet and a glassed in shower.
